summary: 2026 rotating members: Logan (Dallas-hawkish), Hammack (Cleveland-neutral), Kashkari (Minneapolis-neutral/hawkish), Paulson (Philadelphia-dovish). Replacing: Goolsbee, Schmid, Collins, Musalem
content:
Key changes for January 2026 FOMC:

ROTATING OUT:
- Austan Goolsbee (Chicago) - dissented in Dec 2025 wanting to hold
- Jeffrey Schmid (Kansas City) - dissented in Oct/Dec 2025 wanting to hold
- Susan Collins (Boston)
- Alberto Musalem (St Louis)

ROTATING IN:
- Lorie Logan (Dallas) - VERY HAWKISH
- Beth Hammack (Cleveland) - Neutral
- Neel Kashkari (Minneapolis) - Neutral/leaning hawkish
- Anna Paulson (Philadelphia) - Dovish

PERMANENT VOTERS include Stephen Miran (Fed Governor) who has dissented at EVERY meeting since appointment (Sept/Oct/Dec 2025) wanting faster rate cuts.

Market expectation: Fed likely to pause/hold rates in early 2026.
